[01:33.00]Safety regulations in power-stations are very strict.’
[01:36.50]If we spent money on research now, we could develop stations which create their own fuel and burn their own waste.
[01:43.00]In many parts of the world where there are no fossil fuels, nuclear power is the only alternative.
[01:48.00]If you accept that we need electricity, then we will need nuclear energy.
[01:53.00]Just imagine what the world would be like if we didn’t have electricity - no heating, no lighting, no transport, no radio or TV.
[02:01.00]Just think about the ways you use electricity every day.
[02:05.00]Surely we don’t want to go back to the Stone Age.
[02:07.50]That’s what will happen if we turn our backs on nuclear research.’
[02:11.30]<br>
[02:18.30]‘Thank you, Professor. 
[02:19.50]Our next guest is a member of CANE, the Campaign Against Nuclear Energy, Jennifer Hughes.’
[02:25.50]<br>
[02:31.00]‘Right. I must disagree totally with Professor Burnham.
