[02:41.50]Machines fail.
[02:43.20]People make mistakes.
[02:44.70]What would happen if there were a serious nuclear accident?
[02:48.00]And an accident must be inevitable - sooner or later.
[02:51.00]Huge areas would be evacuated, and they could remain contaminated with radioactivity for years.
[02:57.00]If it happened in your area, you wouldn’t get a penny in compensation.
[03:01.00]No insurance company covers nuclear risks.
[03:04.00]There are accidents.
[03:05.70]If the nuclear industry didn’t keep them quiet, there would be a public outcry.
[03:11.00]Radioactivity causes cancer and may affect future generations.
[03:16.00]Next, nuclear waste.
[03:19.00]There is no technology for absolutely safe disposal.
[03:22.50]Some of this waste will remain active for thousands of years.
[03:25.50]Is that what you want to leave to your children?
[03:28.00]And their children’s children?
[03:30.00]A reactor only lasts about 25 years.
[03:33.20]By the year 2000 we’ll have ‘retired’ 26 reactors in the UK.
