[03:41.50]Terrorists could hold the nation to ransom if they captured a reactor.
[03:46.00]In the USA the Savannah River plant, and Professor Burnham knows this very well, lost (yes, ‘lost’) enough plutonium between 1955 and 1978 to make 18 (18!) atom bombs.
[04:02.00]Where is it?
[04:04.00]Who’s got it?
[04:05.50]I consider that nuclear energy is expensive, dangerous, and evil, and most of all, absolutely unnecessary.
[04:16.00]But Dr Woodstock will be saying more about that.’
[04:19.00]<br>
[04:26.00]‘Thank you Jennifer.
[04:27.00]Now I’m very pleased to welcome Dr Catherine Woodstock.
[04:30.50]She is the author of several books on alternative technology.
[04:33.80]<br>
[04:39.50]‘Hello.
[04:40.50]I’d like to begin by agreeing with Jennifer.
[04:46.00]We can develop alternative sources of power, and unless we try we’ll never succeed.
[04:54.00]Instead of burning fossil fuels we should be concentrating on more economic uses of electricity, because electricity can be produced from any source of energy.
[05:10.00]If we didn’t waste so much energy, our resources would last much longer.
[05:16.50]You can save more energy by conservation than you can produce for the same money.
